  exerciseName: ReplaceDuplicatedCode
  exerciseTitle: Replace duplicate code with local function
  exerciseText: Replace the duplicated copy pasted code with multiple calls to a
    local function.
  hintText: Local functions are just like normal functions, except defined inside
    another function and can only be used within that function.
  solutionText: "DoLogic();\r\nDoLogic();\r\nDoLogic();\r\nDoLogic();\r\n\r\nvoid
    DoLogic() {\r\n    position += new Vector3(10, 0, 0);\r\n    rotation += 90;\r\n   
    count++;\r\n    ExerciseValidate(position, rotation, count);\r\n}"
  completedText: Here you learned how to define a local function, this can sometimes
    be a great way to make some function code more readable, assuming that function
    code is only ever used within that function.
